, Humphrey continued Illinois track and field\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dominant run by earning her second-straight Big Ten outdoor long jump title and finishing fourth at the NCAA Championships with a leap of 6.62m (21-8\\u00c2\\u00be).\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1250, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illinois_Fighting_Illini\", \"score\": 0.9998812538424572, \"rank\": 0.00011818876810558912, \"text\": \"Illinois\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illinois_Fighting_Illini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Illinois_Fighting_Illini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s side\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"Humphrey\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"field\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dominant run\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"her second-straight Big Ten outdoor long jump title\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"the NCAA Championships\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"a leap\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"6.62m\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the indoor season, Humphrey won the Big Ten title with a 6.94m (22-9\\u00c2\\u00bc) jump \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 the third-longest leap in NCAA indoor history \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093\\u00c2 and finished as the national runner-up.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999963800862168, \"rank\": 3.6199262803224035e-06, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the indoor season\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1457}, {\"ngram\": \"Humphrey\